  "response": "There are several precise methods for drawing support and resistance lines in forex trading:\n\n1. Price Action Approach\n- Identify clear swing highs and swing lows\n- Look for multiple touches at similar price levels\n- Use clean, horizontal lines\n- Consider timeframe relevance\n\n2. Technical Analysis Methods\n- Use pivot points\n- Fibonacci retracement levels\n- Previous significant market turning points\n- Major psychological price levels\n\n3. Advanced Techniques\n- Multi-timeframe analysis\n- Volume confirmation\n- Use of candlestick patterns\n- Combine multiple indicators\n\n4. Key Criteria for Precision\n- At least 2-3 confirmed touches\n- Strong historical significance\n- Consider overall market context\n- Adjust lines with new price information\n\n5. Recommended Tools\n- MetaTrader platforms\n- TradingView\n- Advanced charting software\n- Professional trading platforms\n\n6. Best Practices\n- Validate lines across different timeframes\n- Regularly review and adjust\n- Don't force lines where they don't naturally exist\n- Consider market volatility\n\nNo single method is universally perfect. Combining multiple approaches and practicing consistently yields the most precise results.",
